            <thetext>genjson.py and gendata.py both work on the Demobrowser&#39;s demos. Their 
functionality is complemental: 

- genjson.py: create config.demo.json, copy demo source JS files to ./script 
(as e.g. demobrowser.demo.animation.Login.src.js)
- gendata.py: create demodata.js, the demo index file used for Demobrowser&#39;s 
tree navigation and search

In merging them, we only have to walk through the list of demos once (instead 
of twice). The whole functionality should also be easier to maintain  in one 
script.</thetext>
